## Relativistic hydrodynamics on 2+1-dimensional curved backgrounds

In the hydrodynamic limit the energy–momentum tensor T^{\mu\nu} of a neutral fluid is a function of the local temperature T(x), of the velocity field u^\mu(x), of the background metric g_{\mu\nu}(x) and of their covariant derivatives.
